Subject: [PATCH] Phase C-6 L54-L57b: klass/method/const-method loads, csp & esp as capabilities

This patch carries the C-6 fixes that took execution from the first
real method's `_return_register_finalizer` (L54) deep into runtime
class loading (RuntimeException, ClassFileParser, create_instance_klass)
and on to bytecode field access. Each fix replaces an integer load/
store/arithmetic that strips a 16-byte capability's tag with a
cap-aware equivalent.

L54  macroAssembler load_klass: with -UseCompressedClassPointers the
     Klass* sits in the oop header as a full capability (markWord 8 +
     8 pad, klass at offset 16). cap-LDR it. Also _return's receiver
     `this` from local 0 -> cap_ldr (templateTable).

L55  ConstMethod*/Method* loaded from the frame or rmethod in narrow(),
     remove_activation(), and the return/deopt/native/exception entries
     (const_offset, max_stack, size_of_parameters, codes_offset) are
     capabilities -> cap-LDR (and cap-ADD for the rbcp codebase).

L56  generate_return_entry_for "Restore machine SP": the stock tail
     (ldr initial_sp; integer sub; andr sp,-16) strips csp's tag.
     Reconstruct csp from the initial_sp CAPABILITY via cap-sub of a
     16-aligned byte delta, installed with the cap-add-reg form
     targeting csp (#31). RESULT: csp comes back tagged
     ([rwRW,0x42482000-0x42682000]).

L57  esp (expression-stack pointer) is a capability: cap-LDR/cap-STR at
     the last_sp / sender_sp frame slots (prepare_to_jump store +
     return/native restores), and a cap-correct native parameter-space
     allocation (esp -= params*16 via cap-sub; csp = esp via cap-mov).

L57b call_VM_base: esp also returns from the codecache<->libjvm
     trampoline detagged (its address is intact and within the stack
     capability). Re-tag esp = csp + (esp_addr - csp_addr) right after
     the rmethod reload, fixing every resolve call_VM (e.g. putfield
     storing an oop). RESULT: esp comes back tagged.

Execution now reaches putfield/getfield field stores. Remaining: an
8-byte expression-stack misalignment (esp lands mid-slot; cap-LDR
SIGBUS BUS_ADRALN) tracked as L58.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

